'''Henry M. Eichner''' (1909–1971) was an [[Americans|American]] medical artist, illustrator and writer. He did covers and illustrations for the [[Los Angeles Science Fantasy Society]]'s magazine ''Shangri L'Affaires''. His nonfiction book on [[Atlantis]], ''[[Atlantean Chronicles]]'', was published by [[Fantasy Publishing Company, Inc.]] in 1971.
