[[File:Professor emeritus Kaare R Norum tilldelas Nordiska Folkhalsopriset 2010.jpg|thumb|Kaare Norum, 2010.]]
'''Kaare Reidar Norum''' (born 24 December 1932) is a Norwegian professor of nutrition.

He was born in [[Oslo]]. He was hired as a [[docent]] at the [[University of Oslo]] in 1969 and advanced to professor in 1972. He served as vice dean of the [[University of Oslo Faculty of Medicine|Faculty of Medicine]] from 1983 to 1985, dean from 1986 to 1988 and rector from 1999 to 2001.<ref name=snl>{{cite encyclopedia|year=|title=Kaare Reidar Norum|encyclopedia=[[Store norske leksikon]]|editor=|publisher=|location=|url=http://www.snl.no/Kaare_Reidar_Norum|language=Norwegian|accessdate=15 August 2016}}</ref>

He is a fellow of the [[Norwegian Academy of Science and Letters]] since 1986; Commander of the [[Order of St. Olav]] in 1999 (Knight since 1992) and Commander of the [[Order of the Polar Star]].<ref name=nbl>{{cite encyclopedia|year=|title=Kaare R Norum|encyclopedia=[[Norsk biografisk leksikon]]|first=Christian A.|last=Drevon|volume=|editor=[[Knut Helle|Helle, Knut]]|publisher=Kunnskapsforlaget|location=Oslo|url=http://nbl.snl.no/Kaare_R_Norum|language=Norwegian|accessdate=15 August 2016}}</ref>

Norum became a member of {{lang|no|Statens ernæringsråd}} in 1971 and has chaired the council several times. He appeared numerous times in the [[Norwegian Broadcasting Corporation]], speaking on topics within nutrition, notably together with [[Ingrid Espelid Hovig]].<ref name=snl/>

