'''Torfinnsvatnet''' is a [[lake]] in the municipality of [[Voss]] in [[Hordaland]] county, [[Norway]]. The {{convert|6.41|km2}} lake lies about {{convert|1.7|km}} east of the lake [[Hamlagrøvatnet]]. The lake has a [[dam]] on the west side, which keeps the water level regulated for the local [[hydroelectric power plant]]s. The river Torfinno connects the lake to the nearby lake Hamlagrøvatnet.<ref name="snl">{{cite web|url=http://snl.no/Torfinno|title=Torfinno|author=Store norske leksikon|authorlink=Store norske leksikon|language=Norwegian|accessdate=2014-05-16}}</ref>
